# Patch: ACP configOptions for codecompanion.nvim model switching (ga keybinding)
#
# Context:
#   codecompanion.nvim uses the ACP (Agent Client Protocol) to communicate with
#   Hermes.  When the user presses `ga` in a chat buffer, codecompanion sends
#   `session/set_config_option` with configId="model".  Before this patch,
#   Hermes only exposed the legacy `models` field (SessionModelState) which
#   codecompanion ignores — it only reads `configOptions`.  Furthermore, the
#   `set_config_option` handler only stored the value without actually switching
#   the model, so `/model` inside Hermes would still show the old model.
#
# What this patch does:
#   1. Adds `_build_config_options()` to `HermesACPAgent` which returns a
#      `SessionConfigOptionSelect(id="model", ...)` populated with models from
#      *all configured* providers (not just the current one).
#   2. Updates `new_session()`, `load_session()`, and `resume_session()` to
#      include `config_options=` in their responses.
#   3. Updates `set_config_option()` so that when `config_id == "model"`, it
#      actually switches the model by re-creating the agent (same logic as
#      `set_session_model`).
#
# Display format in codecompanion picker:
#   "<Provider Label>: <model-id>"  (e.g. "Kimi / Kimi Coding Plan: kimi-for-coding")
#
# Provider filtering:
#   Only providers with credentials are shown.  Checks (in order):
#     - PROVIDER_REGISTRY api_key_env_vars
#     - HERMES_OVERLAYS extra_env_vars
#     - Auth store (~/.hermes/auth.json)
#     - Credential pool (external stores like ~/.codex/auth.json)
#     - AWS SDK (bedrock)
#     - Anthropic external creds (Claude Code OAuth)
#     - LM Studio (LM_API_KEY / LM_BASE_URL)
#
# Logging:
#   INFO: "ACP configOptions: serving N model(s) from M provider(s): ..."
#   INFO: "Session X: model switched to <model> via provider <provider> (via config option)"
#
# Files modified:
#   - acp_adapter/server.py
#   - tests/acp/test_server.py
#
# How to regenerate this patch:
#   cd ~/Codes/hermes-agent
#   # Make your edits to acp_adapter/server.py and tests/acp/test_server.py
#   git diff > ~/.config/nixpkgs/usr/cli/ai/hermes/acp-configOptions.patch
#
# How to rebase if upstream changes conflict:
#   1. Check out the upstream commit that matches your nixpkgs llm-agents pin
#   2. Apply this patch: git apply ~/.config/nixpkgs/usr/cli/ai/hermes/acp-configOptions.patch
#   3. Resolve conflicts, then regenerate with git diff
#
# TODO: Remove this patch once NousResearch/hermes-agent merges equivalent
# functionality upstream.  Track: the PR has not been opened yet (local patch).

